              <p>Some students catch on quickly, but others have a hard time finding <m>p</m> and <m>p^2</m>. In particular, you will probably have to explain that if you know <m>2p</m>, you can find  by multiplying by <m>\frac{1}{2}</m> (and this is the same as dividing by 2.)</p></commentary>
  
  <p>We can turn any quadratic expression into a perfect square by adding the correct constant. This process is called <term>completing the square</term>.</p></task>

